features: ROOM COVERAGE UP TO 698 sq ft (60 min): Ideal for bedrooms, nurseries, kids’ rooms or home office. Purifies 698 sq ft (1x per hour), 349 sq ft (2x per hour) or 144 sq ft (4.8x per hour)
INDEPENDENTLY TESTED AND VERIFIED BY AHAM: CADR (Clean Air Delivery Rate) of 93 CFM for smoke, and 118 CFM for pollen
3-LAYER HEPA FILTRATION: Philips Air Purifier AC0850 removes up to 99.5% of particles as small as 0.003micron*, which is smaller than the smallest known virus
CERTIFIED ALLERGY-FRIENDLY by ECARF (European Center for Allergy Research Foundation): The purifier removes up to 99.99% of pollen, dust mite or pet allergens*
EFFECTIVELY CAPTURES WILDFIRE SMOKE PARTICLES: Use of HEPA air purifiers is considered one of the most effective methods to help protect those in your home during wildfire season
QUIET AND EFFICIENT: In sleep mode, it's quieter than a whisper, with only 19 dB**. Energy-efficient, it uses up to 20W to purify the air, less than a traditional light bulb. Certified Energy Star

SCAN AND VISUALIZE: Professional grade AeraSense sensor accurately scans the air 1000x a second to detect harmful pollutants and intelligently chooses the right speed for every environment. It displays the air quality in real time, with an intuitive color ring (on the product display and in the Air+ app)
CONNECTED WITH AIR+ APP: You can be notified immediately in case of poor air quality, and stay in control – at home or away
THOROUGHLY TESTED FOR QUALITY: Philips has 80+ years of expertise in air care. Our purifiers undergo 170 rigorous tests before release, ensuring top quality

LONG LASTING FILTER WITH SMART CHANGE INDICATOR: The filter lasts up to 1 year***, so you can save money in the long term vs. other air purifiers. Check the filter lifetime indicator in your purifiers digital display, to know when it is time to replace the filter. We recommend using the original Philips filter replacements to get the best performance from your purifier – compatible with FY0293

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: High Performance High Performance Powerful airflow circulation effectively covers rooms up to 698 sq ft (1x per hour) or 144 sq ft (12.5 times per hour) and distributes clean air in every corner of the room. This boosts performance to 93 CFM CADR (Clean Air Delivery rate), independently tested and verified by AHAM. 3- Layer Filtration for up to 99.5% particles removal 3-layer filtration with NanoProtect HEPA, Active Carbon filter and pre-filter captures 99.5% of ultra-fine particles as small as 0.003 microns**, so you are safe from PM2.5, bacteria, pollen, dust, pet dander, odours and other pollutants. Certified by the European Centre for Allergy Research Foundation. Up to 99.9% virus removal Captures aerosols including those which may contain respiratory viruses. Tested independently by airmid health-group to remove up to 99.9% of viruses and aerosols from the air(1).

Intelligent sensors Scans the air 1000x a second to detect ultra fine-particles. Reports the air quality in real time, and intelligently chooses the right speed for your home (in auto mode). Quality you can trust Philips purifiers go through 170 mandatory and strict inspection tests before releasing from factory. They are subjected to rigorous life and durability tests, for continuous operation 24/7. Ultra-quiet operation In Sleep mode, the purifier operates in near silence for clean air while you sleep.

Low energy consumption Thanks to its energy efficient design, the air purifier runs at max. 20 W power. This is equivalent to a standard light bulb. Air quality display See the real-time air quality in your home at a glance. The display shows the level of allergens and PM2.5 with an intuitive color ring

DISCLAIMERS: *From the air that passes through the filter, tested by a 3rd party laboratory. **Calculated average sound pressure at 1.5 meter from the device, based on measurements according to IEC 60704. Sound pressure level depends on room construction, decoration and positioning of device and listener. ***Recommended lifetime is calculated based on the Philips user's average usage time and WHO urban outdoor pollution level data. Actual lifetime is impacted by usage environments and frequencies. ****Alexa and Google Home availability depends on your location. (1) Microbial Reduction Rate Test conducted at Airmid Healthgroup Ltd. in a 28.5m3 test chamber contaminated with airborne influenza A(H1N1). 99.9% removed, in Turbo mode after 10-20 mins, tested in lab setting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: All it takes is 1 pump of my cologne bottle and this thing can detect the smell and goes off cleaning the air within about 1 min of spraying. This happens every time. Very impressed with its ability to detect things in the air.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It can get very loud, but it seems to be effective
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. The hepa filter in this is good and the fan clearly works. It does get a little too loud sometimes, but I have it in a hallway where it usually doesn’t matter. If I’m trying to talk to my daughter from the other end of the hall and this thing is on high, there is no way I’ll be able to understand her response, or even if she said anything. We would have to shout over it. That’s a little annoying, but it can be set to a more quiet mode, so that doesn’t matter to me a lot. TBH. I haven’t even bothered with the app yet, but I will because I want to know if the air quality matches another one I have in the house that shows me on the purifier screen. I think this one is sensitive and kicks on to clean the air whenever it senses anything foreign, so it’s doing its job and it also looks nice! I like the matte surface.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars PHILIPS Air Purifier 800 Series
reviews.reviewText: I like this air purifier. It works well and looks good in our house without being distracting. I have it in our master bedroom and I can't tell a difference in the amount of dust and pet hair from before use of this to after.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Noisy even when completing OFF
reviews.reviewText: It works well, doesn’t move a lot of air even on its highest fan setting though. And it makes a high pitched noise even when totally off. I have to leave it unplugged when it becomes annoying. I must have gotten a defective unit this can’t be normal. This one is trash.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice quiet unit. The filter is a bit weird to change, but works.One thing to note, when you open it there's a sticker that shows you something about the filter. It was a bit confusing, but you have to open it up and remove the plastic sheeting and then put it back in. I found that sticker to be confusing.However, the App works, it's meh - like most of these types of forced to be smart devices. I find an air purifier is one of those set and forget type of things - just give me a notice on device when I need to change the filter, that's about all the smartness I need. Doesn't need to be "smart" - but its there if you are so inclined.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great and is quiet
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I really like this air purifier as i said in the title it really does work well and is very quiet. The app is simple yet efficient and allows you to see what is going on with the device and to control it. The three modes are perfect for whatever you need. Well worth the money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars We love it so far!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve never had an air purifier before, but have been wanting one recently with all the forest fires and a new pup who is making our whole house sneeze, I thought this PHILIPS Air Purifier 800 Series would be a great addition to our home.It’s been great so far! Again, I have never had one before so I do not have anything to compare it to. I do notice us sneezing less and our air quality in our house seems more “fresh”. I know I’m not using it to it’s full potential yet, I’m still learning, but it’s been great so far and I’m sure it will only get better once I really dive in deep learning more about it! But it’s definitely a great air purifier for beginners, like myself!!
